7.03	Paul-%C9mile_Borduas	Paul-Émile Borduas	Paul-Émile Borduas (November 1, 1905 – February 22, 1960) was a Canadian painter known for his abstract paintings. He was also an activist for the separation of church and state, especially for art, in Quebec.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/88/Paul-%C3%89mile_Borduas.JPG/150px-Paul-%C3%89mile_Borduas.JPG
